{"questionId":"20414","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cot</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math> .</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>50</mn><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>cot</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>50</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cot</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></math> may be identified as a length on a diagram, and not written explicitly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20414","referenceCode":"21M.2.AHL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that y=x+50 cot θ .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Reciprocal trig ratios and their pythagorean identities. Inverse circular functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}